{"key":"post-11037523","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>11037523</id>\n<content>The tub with holes was only for colonization.&amp;nbsp; For indoor fruiting, you can use open air and just lay a sheet of plastic loosely over the basket.&amp;nbsp; Lift it up several times per day when you mist.&amp;nbsp; Some growers fruit laundry baskets in open air at normal room humidity, but performance is not as good.&amp;nbsp; If you do it in open air, you'll notice the straw around the edges dries out, which is actually good.&amp;nbsp; The straw inside is still moist, and the dry straw forms somewhat of a 'contamination barrier' protecting what's inside.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>11038686</next>\n<prev>11037395</prev>\n<first>11034421</first>\n<last>11058199</last>\n<when>1252644299</when>\n<utime>09/11/09 07:44 AM</utime>\n</post>"}